to create package -npm init
to install express-npm i express
to run -node file_name .js

basic steps

1.creating a folder-(bankserver)
2.create a package-json file(npm init)
3.create a node module files(npm express)
4.create index.js file
5.import express inside index.js
6.create app using express
7.set up port number
8.resolving http requests
9.install nodemon npm i -g nodemon
10.http response code 
    1xx-information
    2xx-successful
    3xx-redirection
    4xx-client error
    5xx-server error
11.JWT Token -authentication
to check login or not

login -------token generate----->client-----req to deposit+token------>server token check?

install JWT -JSONwebtoken

  npm i jsonwebtoken
  to generate a JWT token -sign()

 12.Middleware- to verify the token 
     -It comes in the middle of the request and response
     -it also provides access to mini functions
        
        1.Application-level middleware
        -For entire application

        2.Router level middleware
        -to verify the token
         to valdate the token -verify()

 13.Database integration

       1)install mongoose- npm i mongoose (for connecting nodejs and mongodb)  
        2)Db connect via mongose
        3) create a model using mongoose

 14) asynchronous function resloving

      1)resolving state -then()
      2)rejection state -catch()            

15) CORS -Cross orgin resourse sharing 
     
      install cors - npm i cors 
